    • Constructor Detail

      • Sequence

        public Sequence​(double time,
                java.lang.String command,
                int id,
                int status)
        Manages the list of service outputs by the server. This list is sorted in ascending order based on customer ID, status and time.
        Parameters:
        time - refers to the time the particular action will happen to the customer.
        command - refers to the string of action the server does to the customer.
        id - refers to the customer id.
        status - refers to the numeric value of the action the server does to the customer.

        public int compareTo​(Sequence seq)
        Manages the sorting order of the priority queue. The strings of actions will be stored in a priority queue and sorted based on the customer id, time and what action is being perfomed.
